        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:16PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Colstrip, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip, Lame Deer, Ashland, Birney Village and Northern Cheyenne
Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
